1. Initialize an instance of the `Queue` class.

2. The `enqueue` method appends an item to the top of both stacks.

3. The `dequeue` method first checks if there are any items in the stacks. If not, it returns `None`. Otherwise, it pops items from both stacks in order until there are no more items left in the top of the second stack. Then it returns the last item in the first stack.

